   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Copy of the report.;To Thrakidas, gymnasiarch, bibliophylax of the archives in the Arsinoite nome, from Petheus the elder, son of Petheus the son of Petheus, from Karanis in the division of Herakleides, a farmer of the estate of Germanicus. There belongs to me in the Herakleides division near Karanis a productive olive grove, in which the trees are old, amounting in all to 11 1/2 arourai; and in the village a house and courtyard in which I dwell, and the half share of a privately owned oilpress and storehouse, and in another place another house and buildings and dovecotes; [and] near Psenarpsenesis a catoecic allotment of five arourai and an olive grove in which [. . . and] near Kerkesoucha [. . .]. Therefore I have presented (this declaration).;[Registered in the . . . year of Tiberius Claudius] Caesar [Augustus Germanicus, . . .] 29. I have signed [. . .].</ab>
         </div>
